#MEM id=next-browser source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/next-browser/SKILL.md
M|next-browser|name: next-browser
M|next-browser|description: CLI tool for inspecting a running Next.js dev app programmatically. Enables Dev/Mia/Quinn to inspect React component trees, capture errors, audit network calls, profile Core Web Vitals, a
M|next-browser|version: 1.0.0
M|next-browser|`@vercel/next-browser` is a CLI that exposes React DevTools and the Next.js dev overlay as shell commands. A persistent Chromium daemon runs in the background; each CLI command sends a JSON-RPC messag
M|next-browser|**When to use:** Any time Dev, Mia, or Quinn needs to inspect what a running Next.js app is actually doing — component state, network calls, render performance, accessibility, or build errors — withou
M|next-browser|**Preferred (integrates with Claude Code):**
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|npx skills add vercel-labs/next-browser
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|**Manual:**
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|pnpm add -g @vercel/next-browser
M|next-browser|playwright install chromium
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser open http://localhost:3000        # launch browser + navigate
M|next-browser|next-browser goto /anl                  # full-page reload to path
M|next-browser|next-browser push /settings                   # client-side navigation (no reload)
M|next-browser|next-browser back                             # previous page
M|next-browser|next-browser reload                           # refresh
M|next-browser|next-browser restart-server                   # reset Next.js dev server + clear cache
M|next-browser|next-browser close                            # terminate daemon
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser snapshot                         # accessibility tree with interactive element refs
M|next-browser|next-browser tree                             # React component hierarchy (full)
M|next-browser|next-browser tree <component-id>              # individual component: props + hooks + state
M|next-browser|next-browser errors                           # build + runtime errors
M|next-browser|next-browser logs                             # dev server stdout
M|next-browser|next-browser browser-logs                     # console.log/warn/error from browser
M|next-browser|next-browser network                          # list all network requests
M|next-browser|next-browser network <idx>                    # inspect specific request (headers, body, rsp)
M|next-browser|next-browser screenshot                       # viewport capture
M|next-browser|next-browser screenshot --full-page          # full scrollable page capture
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser click <ref|text|selector>        # click an element
M|next-browser|next-browser fill <ref|selector> <value>      # type into an input
M|next-browser|next-browser eval <script>                    # run JS in page ctx
M|next-browser|next-browser eval <ref> <script>              # run JS scoped to a component
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser perf                             # Core Web Vitals + React hydration timing
M|next-browser|next-browser renders start                    # begin component render profiling
M|next-browser|next-browser renders stop                     # end profiling + output render counts
M|next-browser|next-browser ppr lock                         # freeze dynamic cnt (inspect PPR shell)
M|next-browser|next-browser ppr unlock                       # restore dynamic cnt
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser page                             # current page metadata
M|next-browser|next-browser project                          # project structure info
M|next-browser|next-browser routes                           # all registered routes
M|next-browser|next-browser action <id>                      # inspect a Server Action
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser open http://localhost:3000
M|next-browser|next-browser goto /anl
M|next-browser|next-browser errors          # check for build/runtime errors first
M|next-browser|next-browser tree            # inspect component hierarchy
M|next-browser|next-browser network         # check which API calls fired and their status
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser goto /war-room
M|next-browser|next-browser network         # list all requests made during page load
M|next-browser|next-browser network 3       # inspect request #3 — headers, body, rsp
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser snapshot        # get accessibility tree
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser perf http://localhost:3000/anl
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|```bash
M|next-browser|next-browser ppr lock        # freeze Suspense boundaries
M|next-browser|next-browser screenshot      # capture static shell
M|next-browser|next-browser tree            # inspect which components are in the shell vs dynamic
M|next-browser|next-browser ppr unlock
M|next-browser|```
M|next-browser|- Next.js dev server must be running (`npm run dev`)
M|next-browser|- Node.js >= 20
M|next-browser|- Chromium (installed via `playwright install chromium`)
M|next-browser|- Works only against localhost dev server — not prd builds